Part 2
------
DH keeps close watch on students' health 25 Mar 2003
The Department of Health (DH) on 25 Mar 2003 confirmed a new case of
atypical pneumonia involving a 6-year-old girl. The Consultant in-charge of
DH's Disease Prevention and Control Unit, Dr Tse Lai-yin, said the girl is
a student of City One Anglo-Chinese Kindergarten in Sha Tin. She is among
the 286 persons confirmed today to have contracted atypical pneumonia. The
girl developed symptoms on 21 Mar 2003 and was admitted to Prince of Wales
Hospital today. Her condition is stable. Dr Tse said the girl had
consulted a private doctor on 14 Mar 2003. The doctor was confirmed to have
contracted atypical pneumonia earlier.
"We are still looking for the source of infection. The health condition of
the girl's family members, classmates, and teachers are also under close
surveillance," Dr Tse said. As a precaution against atypical pneumonia,
the kindergarten and City One Nursery, both of which shared the same
premises, in consultation with DH and the Education and Manpower Bureau,
have decided to close from today to 31 Mar 2003 for disinfection and cleansing.
Dr Tse reminded teachers and parents to be cautious about the health
condition of their students and children and take every possible means to
prevent infection.
Meanwhile, the ninth floor of Metropole Hotel in Ho Man Tin has been
re-opened. The ninth floor was closed for cleansing and disinfection on 19
Mar 2003 following reports that 8 people had contracted atypical pneumonia
during their stay or visit there. The environmental condition of the hotel
is found to be satisfactory.
To enable members of the public to better understand the prevention of
atypical pneumonia, DH in conjunction with Home Affairs Department, will
conduct a series of health talks at the community halls and community
centres in Sha Tin, Happy Valley, Yau Ma Tei, Tsuen Wan, and Tai Po from 26
Mar 2003 to 3 Apr 2003 in the morning and afternoon sessions. The talks
will be conducted in Cantonese. Members of the public who wish to attend
are requested to call 2961 8673 during office hours for details and
reservation.
